I ran for 2 miles before stopping to take a break.

I was in the hospital for 3 days. I ended up with a small amount of brain damage and now I'm deaf in my left ear.

I finally returned home from the hospital, I was so happy to be home. I was so happy to be back with my family. I will never forget that day I ran away from the Bee. I will never forget the day I ran into the tree. I will never forget the day I got brain damage.

Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?". 

I got very scared and I swiped the bee off of me and I started to run away. I ran for 2 miles down our back road  
I was running for my life.
 I was so scared. I was running so fast, I didn't know where I was going. I ended up running into a tree and I fell down. After I ran into the tree I passed out and woke up in the hospital. I was in the hospital for 3 days. I ended up with a small amount of brain damage and now I'm deaf in my left ear.

I finally returned home from the hospital, I was so happy to be home. I was so happy to be back with my family. I will never forget that day I ran away from the Bee. I got very scared and I swiped the bee off of me and I started to run away. I ran for 2 miles down our back road  
I was running for my life.
 I was so scared. I was running so fast, I didn't know where I was going. I ended up running into a tree and I fell down. After I ran into the tree I passed out and woke up in the hospital. I was in the hospital for 3 days. I ended up with a small amount of brain damage and now I'm deaf in my left ear.

I finally returned home from the hospital, I was so happy to be home. I was so happy to be back with my family. I will never forget that day I ran away from the Bee. I will never forget the day I ran into the tree. I will never forget the day I got brain damage. I will never forget the day I got deaf in my left ear. 

I learned that I might as well stay inside to avoid further deafnes

Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?". 

I got very scared and I swiped the bee off of me and I started to run away. I ran for 2 miles down our back road  
I was running for my life.
 I was so scared. I was running so fast, I didn't know where I was going. I ended up running into a tree and I fell down. After I ran into the tree I passed out and woke up in the hospital. I was in the hospital for 3 days. I ended up with a small amount of brain damage and now I'm deaf in my left ear.

I finally returned home from the hospital, I was so happy to be home. I was so happy to be back with my family. I will never forget that day I ran away from the Bee. Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?". 

I got very scared and I swiped the bee off of me and I started to run away. I ran for 2 miles down our back road  
I was running for my life.
 I was so scared. I was running so fast, I didn't know where I was going. I ended up running into a tree and I fell down. After I ran into the tree I passed out and woke up in the hospital. I was in the hospital for 3 days. I ended up with a small amount of brain damage and now I'm deaf in my left ear.

I finally returned home from the hospital, I was so happy to be home. I was so happy to be back with my family. I will never forget that day I ran away from the Bee.
